nchronization"],"visibility":"public","forks":4825,"open_issues":361,"watchers":77447,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/pulls/8427","html_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/pull/8427","diff_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/pull/8427.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/pull/8427.patch","merged_at":"2022-07-22T09:27:59Z"},"body":"### Purpose\r\n\r\nEncrypted folders should not have the fs watcher enabled and rarely benefit from a scheduled rescan.  Versioning does not work well for them either.  The GUI adjusts the suggested settings accordingly (watcher disabled, one day rescan interval, no versioning) when accepting a receive-encrypted folder.  Mirror that behavior to the auto-accept case where the GUI is not involved.\r\n\r\nFor watcher and rescan, the defaults are overridden especially in `handleAutoAccepts()`, while the versioning is filtered out completely in the backend's `FolderConfiguration.prepare()`.\r\n\r\nFixes #8296.\r\n\r\n### Testing\r\n\r\nManual testing with auto-accept enabled or disabled from a certain remote device.\r\n\r\n### Documentation\r\n\r\nIs it worth mentioning this automatic override in the docs?  The only place I've found is at https://docs.syncthing.net/users/config.html#config-option-device.autoacceptfolders, which is pretty terse in general.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/8427/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/8427/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"id":7045070583,"node_id":"CE_lADOAOCAEs5IM6t6zwAAAAGj6z73","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/syncthing/syncthing/issues/events/7045070583","actor":{"l